{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4391771306","title":"CEO Office - AI Accelerator - Lead Builder","company":"noon","location":"Riyadh ","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://ae.linkedin.com/jobs/view/ceo-office-ai-accelerator-lead-builder-at-noon-4391771306?refId=Xhm4k1G%2F1bhEgB7%2Flc%2F2nA%3D%3D&trackingId=vnFfrJWpAE9U8fnlyGnV7w%3D%3D&position=15&pageNum=0","description":"Location: Flexible (Global / Hybrid)Type: Full-timeSponsorship: CEO & Group Leadership\nAbout noon We’re building an ecosystem of digital products and services that power everyday life across the Middle East—fast, scalable, and deeply customer-centric. Our mission is to deliver to every door every day. We want to redefine what technology can do in this region, and we’re looking for an AI Accelerator- Lead Builder who can help us move even faster.\nnoon’s mission: Every door, every day.\nNot “just an engineer”\nThis role sits at the intersection of applied research, product invention, and AI-powered software craftsmanship.\nWe’re building an AI Office inside noon - a highly leveraged group that lives above squads and product lines, spotting opportunities others miss and solving them with working software.\nYou won’t be assigned tickets. You’ll define, build, and ship.\nYour vantage point\n● Full visibility across noon’s organization● Briefed directly by the CEO and leadership team● Not embedded in a traditional hierarchy● Direction & accountability driven by impact, not process\nThis is a Staff-level product builder + internal founder + applied AI researcher role — a rare blend of curiosity, speed, and execution.\nWhat you build (three pillars)\n1️. Group leverage & accelerationYou build tools, workflows, and systems that meaningfully compress time, reduce friction, and increase velocity across teams.\nThis is about leverage over load - software that amplifies thousands of human hours into hundreds.\n2️. Rapid capability injection into missionsYou identify high-value features or enhancements teams can’t prioritize - and you ship them within days.\nNot slow quarters. Not remote roadmaps. But fast, targeted additions that unlock disproportionate value.\n3️. Prototypes for things that don’t yet existYou will build working prototypes for future businesses, products, and ideas before they have names or teams. No slides. No long discovery cycles. Just shipping real software to uncover real signals. You act as a product accelerator, quarterbacking ideas end-to-end.\nHow we work\n● Bias toward rapid iteration● Nothing should take more than one week to production● Early momentum beats polish● Working software is the primary deliverable\nBuild → ship → learn → repeat\nAt noon, speed, clarity, and momentum matter more than perfection in early stages.\nTech stack - where you’ll operate\nWe build on Google Cloud Platform (GCP) with a Python-first philosophy.\nCore technologies you’ll use\n● Python (backend, data, AI tooling)● GCP services: Cloud Functions, BigQuery, Cloud Run, Pub/Sub, Vertex AI● Modern frontend frameworks (React / Next.js) as needed● CI/CD pipelines (Cloud Build / GitHub Actions)● AI stacks (OpenAI, Vertex AI models) integrated deeplySuccess here means mastering full-stack product outcomes with a Python + GCP core.\nWho this role is for\nYou might call yourself a builder, a creator, a hacker, or even a researcher - but titles aren’t what matter. This role is for someone who:● Thinks in systems, leverage, and emergent patterns● Sees opportunities others miss● Has shipped side projects that taught them something real● Loves fast, iterative software cycles● Is comfortable with ambiguity and shaping problems, not just solving them● Can own outcomes, not tasks\nShip something that speaks\nOne way we evaluate fit for this role is through your side projects or personal builds. We want to see things you’ve shipped that reflect curiosity, speed, impact, playfulness, and technical depth. Share your side gigs. Show us what you built. Let your code do the talking.\nYour toolkit\nEngineering\n● Python backend & APIs● Full-stack development when needed● GCP deployment & observability● Data pipelines & real-time workflows\nProduct\n● Rapid UX experimentation● Hypothesis → prototype → learn cycles● Minimal, delightful interfaces\nAI-native\n● Vertex AI / LLM integrations● Embeddings, agents, workflows● AI-assisted development, testing, and deliveryYou treat AI as a force multiplier, not a buzzword.\nWhat makes this role rare\n● CEO & leadership sponsorship● No bureaucracy - you ship, not queue● Organization-wide impact● Turn intent into production in days● Founding influence on how noon builds software\nWhat success looks like\n● Tools that materially accelerate execution across teams● Live prototypes driving new strategic directions● Frequent weekly shipping with measurable impact● A track record of transforming ideas into working systems● A reputation as the person who just builds it"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4390949405","title":"Channel Sales Executive","company":"Ansys","location":"Canonsburg","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://ae.linkedin.com/jobs/view/channel-sales-executive-at-ansys-4390949405?refId=Xhm4k1G%2F1bhEgB7%2Flc%2F2nA%3D%3D&trackingId=JyuBT4zQxJSg%2BeDsbGd2rg%3D%3D&position=18&pageNum=0","description":"We Are:At Synopsys, we drive the innovations that shape the way we live and connect. Our technology is central to the Era of Pervasive Intelligence, from self-driving cars to learning machines. We lead in chip design, verification, and IP integration, empowering the creation of high-performance silicon chips and software content. Join us to transform the future through continuous technological innovation.\nYou Are:You are a dynamic and driven sales professional who thrives in collaborative environments and is passionate about building strong partnerships. With a proven track record in the software industry, you understand the nuances of both indirect and direct sales, excelling at developing and nurturing relationships with channel partners and customers alike. Your consultative approach allows you to identify and address customer needs, ensuring optimal solutions and satisfaction at every touchpoint.You bring a strategic mindset to your work, leveraging data and market insights to inform your sales strategies and drive sustainable growth. Your leadership capabilities shine as you coach and motivate partner representatives, empowering them to reach new heights in their performance. Adaptable and resourceful, you navigate complex situations with ease, mediating issues and facilitating effective resolutions to maintain momentum and trust.Your communication and negotiation skills are second to none, enabling you to engage confidently with senior executives and key stakeholders across diverse cultures. Committed to continuous learning, you stay abreast of industry trends and best practices, ensuring you bring the latest thinking to every engagement. Fluent in English and Polish, you possess cultural sensitivity and a global perspective that enhances your effectiveness in a multinational environment. Above all, you are passionate about technology and innovation, eager to contribute to Synopsys’ mission and make a lasting impact in the region.\nWhat You’ll Be Doing:Driving sales of ANSYS, part of Synopsys solutions within a specified region through channel partners, embodying ANSYS, part of Synopsys Channel principles.Owning and executing the sales plan for your territory, ensuring growth targets are consistently met.Providing hands-on leadership for sales opportunities and guiding channel partner reps with a “sell-with” approach.Building and nurturing relationships with senior-level customer executives to unlock new market opportunities.Coaching and motivating channel partner representatives to enhance their ANSYS, part of Synopsys selling skills and performance.Conducting joint customer visits and ensuring timely completion of sales, technical, and principal trainings and certifications.Delivering accurate and timely sales forecasts; regularly reviewing pipeline and forecast with channel partners.Managing partner capacity and capabilities to ensure optimal coverage and effectiveness.Serving as the central point of contact for all sales matters at the partner, ensuring efficient workflows.Implementing ANSYS, part of Synopsys Partner Program initiatives, including marketing programs, to drive regional success and future growth.Mediating channel partner requests/issues and assisting in tactical solution strategies for customer satisfaction.Collaborating with ANSYS, part of Synopsys regional sales leaders to analyse market trends and define go-to-market strategies.\nThe Impact You Will Have:Accelerating sales growth and market penetration for ANSYS, part of Synopsys solutions in DubaiEmpowering channel partners with the skills and resources needed to succeed in a highly competitive market.Shaping the future of simulation and PLM software adoption among small and medium-sized businesses.Enhancing customer satisfaction and loyalty through effective resolution of issues and proactive engagement.Driving best practices in channel sales, contributing to Synopsys’ reputation as an industry leader.Supporting the implementation and success of the ANSYS, part of Synopsys Partner Program, fostering long-term growth.Contributing to strategic decisions through market analysis and feedback, shaping regional business direction.Facilitating seamless collaboration between channel partners and internal Synopsys teams for efficient operations.\nWhat You’ll Need:Bachelor’s degree in a technical, engineering, business, or related field.6+ years of successful sales, key accounts, and indirect channel account management experience in the software industry, OR 8+ years of relevant experience.Demonstrated understanding of scientific or technical software products/services, including pricing and licensing practices.Proven consultative selling skills and experience with complex sales cycles.Exceptional contract negotiation abilities with key accounts.Strong analytical, planning, and organizational skills.Fluent in English; Arabic language skills are a plus.Excellent time management, communication, and presentation skills.Ability to travel up to 50% of the time.MBA or advanced degree, and experience in simulation/PLM software industry are preferred.\nWho You Are:A collaborative leader who inspires and motivates others.Strategic thinker with a proactive approach to problem-solving.Effective communicator, able to engage with stakeholders at all levels.Adaptable and resilient, thriving in fast-paced environments.Customer-centric, always striving to deliver exceptional value.Detail-oriented with strong organizational skills.Committed to continuous personal and professional growth.\nThe Team You’ll Be A Part Of:You’ll join a high-performing, collaborative sales team focused on driving growth through strategic partnerships and channel excellence. The team is passionate about delivering value to customers and partners, leveraging deep industry expertise and innovative sales strategies. You’ll work closely with regional leadership, technical sales, marketing, and operational teams to ensure seamless execution and continuous improvement in channel engagement.\nRewards and Benefits:We offer a comprehensive range of health, wellness, and financial benefits to cater to your needs. Our total rewards include both monetary and non-monetary offerings. Your recruiter will provide more details about the salary range and benefits during the hiring process.\nAt Synopsys, we want talented people of every background to feel valued and supported to do their best work. Synopsys considers all applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, military veteran status, or disability.\n#LI-Remote, #LI-Hybrid, #AnsysJob"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4392911479","title":"CTO / Co-Founder - AI Coding Software","company":"Codelogs.ai","location":"Dubai, United Arab Emirates","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://ae.linkedin.com/jobs/view/cto-co-founder-ai-coding-software-at-codelogs-ai-4392911479?refId=Xhm4k1G%2F1bhEgB7%2Flc%2F2nA%3D%3D&trackingId=ZKBncgkry6bC7tlj4nJavg%3D%3D&position=7&pageNum=0","description":"90% of vibe coding projects never become real software.People build fast. They generate features, fix bugs, add pages.But they can't ship. Because they have no idea what they actually built.No structure. No tracking. No path to production.\nThat's not a tool problem. That's a category gap — and nobody's closing it.We are.\nCodelogs.ai turns AI-coded projects into real, shippable software. The operating system above Lovable, Bolt, and V0.\nBuilt. Live. First users in. First positive market and pmf signals received. Target: €1M MRR. 12 months. Max 10 people.\n---\nWe're hiring a CTO. Co-Founder Level.\nNot a senior engineer. Not a tech lead.\nYou are the engineering team. You ship. You talk to users. You track what's working. You iterate. Daily. No manager sets your priorities. No PM writes your tickets. You open Claude Code at 7am because you already know what to build next.\nThe product is built: Chrome Extension, full-stack, clean codebase, documented. Clean handover on day one. You're not starting from scratch. You're taking it to exit.\nWhat that means day-to-day:→ Ship working product every single day: features, fixes, experiments→ Own the product end-to-end: architecture, performance, new features→ Run customer interviews yourself. Find patterns, feed them into the roadmap→ Build and own the data layer: usage tracking, retention signals, drop-off points→ Use Claude Code / Cursor as your primary build method→ Make product decisions - you won't be handed a spec sheet→ Lay the foundation so that when we hire, onboarding takes days, not months\nRemote. Fully available. Full product ownership. \nYou're not working for a first-time founder.Volker Hein. Former SAP CTO, responsible for sales in 16 countries. Spent the last 5 years building a 7-figure consulting business helping software CEOs scale and exit. He founded Codelogs out of his own frustration with AI-driven development. This is hands-on with someone who's actually done it.\n---\nYou're a fit if:You've done this before. You've taken a product from early traction to exit or close enough that you know what that year actually costs.You ship the day the idea lands, not the day the spec is approved.You read your own metrics. You fix things before anyone asks.Speed isn't your goal, it's your default.→ You've shipped full-stack products solo or in a very tiny team→ You've worked with Chrome Extensions or browser-native environments→ You write clean code fast and know when \"clean enough to ship\" is the right call→ You treat customer conversations as engineering input, not a distraction→ You use AI coding tools at an agentic level, not Copilot autocomplete, actual workflows→ You instrument your own features and actually look at the data\nNot for you if:→ You want \"frontend\" or \"backend\", not both and everything else→ You need someone to write the tickets→ You prefer planning over shipping→ You're not comfortable talking directly to customers---This is a 996 role. Founder-level responsibility, founder-level upside.If that sounds exhausting, this isn't for you.If that sounds like finally the right room, read on.\nCompensation: Equity-based compensation. Discussed openly.\n---\nTo apply, pick one:1. Send a 60-second Loom: a product you shipped and what broke along the way2. One paragraph: the hardest technical decision you made under pressure and would you make it again?3. DM me with what you'd build in the first 30 days at Codelogs and why"}
