{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4393938434","title":"Controller (US Vacation Rentals)","company":"Howard","location":"Miami Beach","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://ats.rippling.com/howard-financial/jobs/7d520ed0-994d-44a4-ab11-d871fac2fdb7?jobSite=LinkedIn","description":"Howard Financial is a full-service back-office solution for high-growth companies with bookkeeping, payroll, and bespoke reporting needs that require accuracy, timeliness, and institutional-quality reporting without the burden of full-time staff. We are an experienced team of bookkeepers and administrators with multiple decades of combined experience across industries allowing companies to focus on their core business while we handle the rest.\n\nFounded in 2023, our team of ~100 professionals supports ~75 clients across a diverse range of industries. We recently reached $6M of contracted ARR and are growing rapidly (over 200% LTM growth).\n\nAs a Controller at Howard, you will be responsible for the financial integrity of a portfolio of Vacation Rental clients. You will bridge the gap between day-to-day bookkeeping and executive-level financial strategy. This role requires a professional who deeply understands the unique accounting challenges of the Short-Term Rental (STR) industry, including trust accounting, owner statements, and merchant processing reconciliations.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nFinancial Oversight: Manage the full month-end close process for multiple STR clients, ensuring Profit & Loss statements and Balance Sheets are accurate and ready for leadership review.Trust Accounting & Owner Statements: Oversee the reconciliation of guest payments, security deposits, and cleaning fees. Ensure owner statements are generated accurately and distributions are processed on time.KPI Analysis: Track and report on industry-specific metrics such as RevPAR (Revenue Per Available Room), ADR (Average Daily Rate), and Occupancy rates to provide actionable insights to clients.Audit & Compliance: Review the work performed by staff accountants and bookkeepers, ensuring all entries align with US GAAP and client-specific Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs).System Integration: Manage data flow between Property Management Systems (PMS) like Guesty, Hostaway, or Streamline and accounting platforms (QuickBooks Online/NetSuite).Client Communication: Serve as the primary point of contact for financial inquiries, explaining variances and providing clarity on financial performance during monthly reviews.\n\nRequirements & Qualifications\n\nIndustry Experience (MANDATORY): At least 4+ years of direct experience as an Accountant or Senior Accountant specifically within the US Vacation Rental / Short-Term Rental (STR) industry.Accounting Foundation: Bachelor’s degree in Accounting or Finance. A solid understanding of US GAAP is required.Technical Stack: Advanced proficiency in QuickBooks Online and experience with at least one PMS (e.g., Guesty, Hostaway, Streamline, Track).Analytical Skills: Expert-level Excel skills (VLOOKUPs, Pivot Tables, data cleaning) for reconciling complex reservation reports.English Proficiency: Exceptional written and verbal communication skills (C1/C2 level) for direct client interaction.Growth Mindset: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and adapt to new technologies and client workflows quickly.\n\nWhat We Offer\n\nCompetitive Compensation: Fixed monthly payment in US Dollars.Performance Incentives: Quarterly bonuses based on performance and quality metrics.Career Path: Bi-annual reviews (July & December) with opportunities to transition into a Senior Controller or Vertical Lead role.Flexibility: 100% remote work with a supportive global culture.Time Off: 10 paid national holidays per year and unlimited PTO after 6 months of tenure."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4390031744","title":"GCC Sales Director - Qatar","company":"MOZN","location":"Al Qirawan","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://ats.rippling.com/mozn-ai/jobs/66ee4599-8429-455e-a5eb-3bf6bc834e31?jobSite=LinkedIn","description":"About Mozn\n\nMOZN is a leading Enterprise AI company enabling organizations to make informed decisions in two critical domains: Financial Crime Prevention and Enterprise Knowledge Intelligence.\n\nWe’re a diverse, collaborative team of innovators united by a shared purpose: to build AI that delivers tangible business value, builds trust, and empowers people and organizations with augmented intelligence. Our culture is built on the relentless pursuit of excellence and meaningful impact.\n\nIf you’re passionate about working alongside exceptional talent on world-class AI, and you want the autonomy and runway to do the best work of your career, join us in shaping the future of intelligent enterprises.\n\nAbout The Role\n\nAs the Sales Director, you will be responsible for leading the sales strategy, business development, and revenue growth of MOZN. You will work closely with Government, financial institutions, fintech companies, and large enterprises to identify opportunities, establish partnerships, and close high-value deals. The ideal candidate has a strong background in LLMS, AML, fraud prevention, and experience in fast-growing B2B SaaS/tech companies.\n\nWhat You'll Do\n\nDevelop and execute a comprehensive sales and business development strategy to expand MOZN’s market presence for FOCAL and OSOS. Identify and engage with key decision-makers in government, banks, fintech firms, regulators, and large enterprises to drive adoption of LLMS/ AML and fraud prevention solutions. Manage the end-to-end sales cycle, from lead generation and qualification to contract negotiation and closing. Build and maintain long-term relationships with strategic clients, partners, and stakeholders. Stay updated on regulatory changes, industry trends, and competitive landscape to position MOZN as a market leader. Work closely with product, marketing, and customer success teams to align sales strategies with business objectives. Represent MOZN at industry events, conferences, and client meetings to promote brand awareness and thought leadership. Utilize CRM tools and data-driven insights to track performance and optimize sales efforts \n\nQualifications\n\n10+ years GCC enterprise B2B sales experience, preferably within Financial Crime, AML, Risk, Compliance, or RegTech. Proven delivery of multi-million USD annual quotas, with a clear record of overachievement. Experience closing complex, multi-stakeholder deals ($1M+), including RFP-driven enterprise sales. Deep solution-selling capability — able to position business value, and ROI (not product-led selling). Strong regional network across tier-1 banks, fintechs, regulators, or government entities — recognized and credible in-market. Demonstrated ability to open doors independently and build pipeline without relying on brand strength. Experience building or scaling a market/territory from limited presence. Enterprise sales discipline: structured forecasting, 3–4x pipeline coverage mindset, CRM hygiene, executive engagement. Background from recognised regional or global enterprise technology firms. Senior presence, commercially mature, able to represent the company at C-level without supervision. \n\nBenefits\n\nYou will be at the forefront of an exciting time for the Middle East, joining a high-growth rocket-ship in an exciting space. You will be given a lot of responsibility and trust. We believe that the best results come when the people responsible for a function are given the freedom to do what they think is best. The fundamentals will be taken care of: competitive compensation, top-tier health insurance, and an enabling culture so that you can focus on what you do best You will enjoy a fun and dynamic workplace working alongside some of the greatest minds in AI. We believe strength lies in difference, embracing all for who they are and empowered to be the best version of themselves."}
