{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4390924649","title":"Segment Solution Technology Lead - Healthcare","company":"Schneider Electric","location":"Rueil Malmaison","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://careers.se.com/jobs/109755?lang=en-us&iis=Job+Board&iisn=linkedin&src=linkedin","description":"Schneider Electric is a global leader in energy management, industrial automation, and digital transformation technologies, operating in more than 100 countries. We believe that access to energy and digital technology is a fundamental human right. Our purpose is to empower everyone to make the most of their energy and resources, bridging progress and sustainability for all.\n\nOur mission is to be the Energy Technology Partner for our customers - leading the electrification, automation, and digitalization of every industry, business, and home to drive efficiency, resilience, and sustainability. This mission builds on our commitment to act as our customers’ best digital partner for sustainability and efficiency by integrating advanced energy technologies, digital solutions, and domain expertise.\n\nWe drive digital transformation by integrating world-leading energy and automation technologies. This includes:\n\nEnd-to-end integration, from connected products to edge control and cloud applications.Lifecycle services, from design and build to operate and maintain, powered by digital twins and AI-enabled insights.Enterprise-wide optimization, transforming operations from site-level to multi-site organizational performance.Integrated platforms, including EcoStruxure™, enabling safe, reliable, efficient, and cybersecure environments across buildings, homes, data centers, infrastructure, and industryDescription of the role & responsibilities of the Segment Solution and Technology Lead \n\nThe Segment Solution and Technology Lead is a role, with a specific intent to focus on complex digital building applications in the Healthcare sector. The role functionally reports into the Building Segment Solutions Director as part of the solutions specialist’s team with the mandate to focus on all opportunities involving complex IT/OT architectures across the Healthcare Segment.\n\nThe role plays a critical role in advancing digital transformation across healthcare facilities by shaping solution architectures, driving innovation with the Line of Business (LoB), and supporting strategic customer engagements. This role blends technical depth, account leadership, and solution evangelism, ensuring Schneider Electric delivers differentiated value in healthcare environments.\n\nYou will act as a trusted advisor to healthcare customers, guiding them through IT/OT convergence, energy and operational efficiency improvements, and the adoption of advanced digital building technologies.\n\nThe Healthcare Segment Solution and Technology Lead will be the catalyst and champion of innovation for Healthcare facilities and will be responsible for driving innovation, and influencing and supporting strategic customers in the digitalization of their buildings’ portfolio.\n\nKey Responsibilities And Deliverables\n\nDrive Innovation & Collaboration with Line of Business (LoB)\n\nServe as a catalyst for innovation across healthcare solutions by working closely with LoB leaders, R&D, offer managers, and solution owners to shape new offers and solution architectures.Contribute to the development of healthcare‑specific solution roadmaps, use cases, and reference architectures.Advocate for segment needs and ensure healthcare requirements influence future products and platform evolution.Participate in solution catalog development, documentation refinement, and strategic solution governance activities.\n\nCustomer & Account Leadership\n\nAct as a trusted technology partner for healthcare customers, advising on digital transformation, modernization, and resilience strategies.Support strategic pursuits across major healthcare accounts in coordination with Account Managers, Segment Leaders, and Solution Architects.Manage executive‑level relationships and position Schneider Electric as a visionary and value‑oriented partner.Influence specifications and consultant ecosystems to shape demand and steer customer decisions in Schneider Electric’s favor. Insights from healthcare team interactions and consultant influence discussions support this (e.g., Healthcare Solutions Community\n\nSolution Architecture & Technical Leadership\n\nLead the definition of end‑to‑end IT/OT architectures for healthcare facilities, including data strategy, integration, system interoperability, and analytics requirements.Shape conceptual and high‑level solution designs using Schneider Electric’s digital platforms, energy technologies, software, and services.Ensure alignment with healthcare‑specific needs such as critical environments, safety, compliance, and cybersecurity.Support complex deals by preparing architectural deliverables, technical value propositions, and solution narratives.\n\nWorkshop Facilitation & Technical Engagements\n\nFacilitate customer workshops covering digital building transformation, energy efficiency, FDD (fault detection diagnostics), IoT, and smart hospital solutions.Translate customer challenges into solution requirements and actionable architectural proposals.Present demos, reference architectures, and case studies to educate customers and internal teams.Bring in best practices from healthcare multi‑system design conversations and Building Advisor use cases mentioned in internal exchanges.Training / upskilling zones and country operations teams through healthcare segment specialisation training Upskilling teams to deliver partner / EcoXpert training\n\nCross‑Functional Collaboration & Ecosystem Enablement\n\nWork with regional and global stakeholders—Segment Leaders, Solution Architects, Marketing, LoBs, and Partner Ecosystems—to ensure solutions land successfully in the field.Provide guidance to local teams, acting as an advanced support and coaching resource, particularly in priority growth regions.Strengthen relationships with engineering firms, integrators, and consultants influencing healthcare projects.\n\nThought Leadership & Best Practice Development\n\nCreate repeatable frameworks, templates, and best practices to scale Healthcare digital solutions globally.Partner with marketing and the segment team to build training materials, reference architectures, and whitepapers showcasing Schneider Electric’s leadership.Contribute content to internal platforms (e.g., Solutions Catalogue, Healthcare Playbooks) and support continuous improvement of documentation processes.\n\nOpportunity Support & Deal Acceleration\n\nSupport the end‑to‑end pursuit lifecycle: opportunity qualification, scoping, solutioning, proposal development, and closing.Help prioritize strategic accounts and segment opportunities based on market signals and portfolio strengths.Leverage deep knowledge of digital hospitals, energy management, microgrids, and hybrid cloud/on‑prem architectures to accelerate the design of winning offers. Requirements for the roleCustomer-centric mindset: excellent customer relationship skills. Ability to create relationships quickly across customers’ organizations. 10+ years experience within the Healthcare Segment proofing her/his knowledge in this fieldPractical experience working in the Healthcare environment, with experience in deploying complex multi-site software solutions with a wide range of integrationsAwareness of RESTful standards and web API's and good knowledge of standard building protocolsGood understanding of networks and network designExperience in the development and influence of specifications to embed software in project requirements Strong capacity to foster collaboration & networking, and work transversally across the organizationStructured way of working; Good attention to detailConfident speaker able to lead technical workshops with customersInternational, multi-cultural mind-set and approachBusiness Developer - Resourceful and self-starter attitude, interest to roll-up one sleeves, get things done and push the organization to deliverTeam Player - Passionate and dynamic professional with the energy and ability to build trust and foster collaboration across a complex matrix environment; Collaborative team-oriented style.\n\nRole Model - Demonstrates strong personal leadership in line with Schneider Electric values.\n\n10 + years of experience in HealthcareGood knowledge and practical experience in executing or providing design consultancy in building automation and energy management systems, enterprise systems and systems integrationGood knowledge of electrical distribution with experience in distributed energy resources and microgridsExcellent networking capabilities and the ability to lead other teams and groups.Market: experience within the Healthcare industryEducation: Bachelor’s degree, Masters’ degree in a relevant field, Computer Engineering or Computer Sciences is a plusLanguages: Fluency in spoken and written English; Any other language is a plusOther: excellent MS PowerPoint and Excel skills, and presentation writing skills\n\nLooking to make an IMPACT with your career?\n\nWhen you are thinking about joining a new team, culture matters. At Schneider Electric, our values and behaviors are the foundation for creating a great culture to support business success. We believe that our IMPACT values – Inclusion, Mastery, Purpose, Action, Curiosity, Teamwork – starts with us.\n\nIMPACT is also your invitation to join Schneider Electric where you can contribute to turning sustainability ambition into actions, no matter what role you play. It is a call to connect your career with the ambition of achieving a more resilient, efficient, and sustainable world.\n\nWe are looking for IMPACT Makers; exceptional people who turn sustainability ambitions into actions at the intersection of automation, electrification, and digitization. We celebrate IMPACT Makers and believe everyone has the potential to be one.\n\nBecome an IMPACT Maker with Schneider Electric – apply today!\n\n€36 billion global revenue\n\n+13% organic growth\n\n150 000+ employees in 100+ countries\n\n#1 on the Global 100 World’s most sustainable corporations\n\nYou must submit an online application to be considered for any position with us. This position will be posted until filled.\n\nSchneider Electric aspires to be the most inclusive and caring company in the world, by providing equitable opportunities to everyone, everywhere, and ensuring all employees feel uniquely valued and safe to contribute their best. We mirror the diversity of the communities in which we operate, and ‘inclusion’ is one of our core values. We believe our differences make us stronger as a company and as individuals and we are committed to championing inclusivity in everything we do. \n\nAt Schneider Electric, we uphold the highest standards of ethics and compliance, and we believe that trust is a foundational value. Our Trust Charter is our Code of Conduct and demonstrates our commitment to ethics, safety, sustainability, quality and cybersecurity, underpinning every aspect of our business and our willingness to behave and respond respectfully and in good faith to all our stakeholders. You can find out more about our Trust Charter here\n\nSchneider Electric is an Equal Opportunity Employer. It is our policy to provide equal employment and advancement opportunities in the areas of recruiting, hiring, training, transferring, and promoting all qualified individuals regardless of race, religion, color, gender, disability, national origin, ancestry, age, military status, sexual orientation, marital status, or any other legally protected characteristic or conduct."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4371789136","title":"Sales Specialist - Data & AI Security","company":"Veeam Software","location":"Seattle","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://careers.veeam.com/job/-/-/22681/91673099136?gh_src=f754f242teu","description":"Veeam is the Data and AI Trust Company, specializing in helping organizations ensure their data and AI are fully understood, secured, and resilient to enable the acceleration of safe AI at scale. As the market leader in both data resilience and data security posture management, Veeam is built for the convergence of identity, data, security, and AI risk. Headquartered in Seattle with offices in more than 30 countries, Veeam protects over 550,000 customers worldwide, who trust Veeam to keep their businesses running. Join us as we go fearlessly forward together, growing, learning, and making a real impact for some of the world’s biggest brands.\n\nAbout The Role\n\nVeeam, following its acquisition of Securiti AI - the leader in AI-powered data security posture management (DSPM) - is seeking experienced Sales Specialists to drive growth in this innovative business.\n\nIn this role, you will focus exclusively on Securiti AI solutions, working closely with Veeam account executives to cross-sell into Veeam’s customer base, win new business, and expand existing Securiti AI accounts. You’ll have a shared territory with multiple AEs, strong earning potential, and support from a dedicated Securiti AI solution engineer for technical engagements. You’ll also benefit from Veeam’s robust go-to-market resources to ensure customer success.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\nDevelop and execute a territory plan to drive repeatable revenue within assigned accounts.Collaborate with account executives to identify and maximize cross-sell opportunities for Securiti AI solutions.Lead the entire sales process, serving as a trusted advisor, and presenting compelling business cases to customers.Manage a pipeline of high-value opportunities, ensuring accurate forecasting and CRM discipline.Expand relationships with key channel partners and resellers to accelerate deal flow and market reach. \n\nWhat You’ll Bring\n\nProven success closing complex enterprise software deals, with 10-15+ years in security software sales.Extensive experience managing multithreaded sales cycles involving multiple stakeholders.Strong existing relationships with C-suite executives and channel partners in large enterprises.Deep understanding of enterprise software sales, particularly in data security, management, or cybersecurity.Reputation for integrity, honesty, and building long-term customer relationships. \n\nWhat You’ll Get\n\nVeeam offers benefits that support your whole self:\n\n25 paid vacation days plus RTT days, plus 4 extra global VeeaMe Days for self-care and 24 paid volunteer hours annually through Veeam CaresMandatory public health insurance with broad medical coverageEmployer-paid private medical, dental, optical, and wellness plan through Axa, with options for dependentsLife insurance with enhanced coverage above the Social Security ceilingEducation pension for dependent children up to age 26 if in full-time educationState and supplementary pension contributions by VeeamOpportunities to learn and grow through on-demand libraries (LinkedIn Learning, O’Reilly), mentoring, workshops and learning events like our annual Global Day of Learning\n\nPlease note: If an applicant is permanently located outside of France, Veeam reserves the right to decline the application for this position\n\nVeeam Software is an equal opportunity employer and does not tolerate discrimination in any form on the basis of race, color, religion, gender, age, national origin, citizenship, disability, veteran status or any other classification protected by federal, state or local law. All your information will be kept confidential.\n\nPlease note that any personal data collected from you during the recruitment process will be processed in accordance with our Recruiting Privacy Notice.\n\nThe Privacy Notice sets out the basis on which the personal data collected from you, or that you provide to us, will be processed by us in connection with our recruitment processes.\n\nBy applying for this position, you consent to the processing of your personal data in accordance with our Recruiting Privacy Notice.\n\nBy submitting your application, you acknowledge that the information provided in your job application and any supporting documents is complete and accurate to the best of your knowledge. Any misrepresentation, omission, or falsification of information may result in disqualification from consideration for employment or, if discovered after employment begins, termination of employment.\n\n\n\n"}
