inancial targets. If you thrive in a fast-paced and results-driven role and want to work to build a world-class Sales and Channel Management organization—read on.\n\nIn This Role, You Will Have The Opportunity To\n\nDevelop and execute Country/Regional strategy to maximize revenue and increase market share for all company portfolio products including Advanced Staining, Core Histology, and Pathology Imaging.Own and lead relationships with key Accounts, driving long-term brand advocacy and increasing brand loyalty across the Healthcare ecosystem.Track partner KPIs including pipeline, revenue, and win rates while identifying underperforming partners and implementing improvement plans.Directly present Leica Biosystems solutions to end customers, including histopathologists and laboratory managers.Collaborate with internal stakeholders (Marketing, Finance, Customer Care) to act as a partner advocate for accurate decision making.\n\nThe Essential Requirements Of The Job Include\n\nEducation: Educated to bachelor’s degree level from related field.Experience: Multiple years of proven experience (minimum five years) in Channel Partner Management.Technical/Scientific: Scientific background or demonstrated expertise in histopathology with the ability to initiate new scientific solutions directly to Lab managers.Commercial Skills: Proven consultative selling skills within a complex sales environment and financial acumen regarding budgets and forecasting.Communication & Mobility: Fluent in English and able to accommodate extensive travel requirements of more than 60%.\n\nIt would be a plus if you also possess previous experience in:\n\n3-5 years previous experience in Histopathology businessStrong track records of managing channel partner and achieving commercial goals.Familiar with working in multinational environment.\n\nAt Leica Biosystems, we believe in designing a better, more sustainable workforce. We recognize the benefits of flexible, remote working arrangements for eligible roles and are committed to providing enriching careers, no matter the work arrangement. You will be in the field but will be required to be in our office in Dubai on a regular base.\n\nJoin our winning team today. Together, we’ll accelerate the real-life impact of tomorrow’s science and technology. We partner with customers across the globe to help them solve their most complex challenges, architecting solutions that bring the power of science to life.\n\nFor more information, visit www.danaher.com."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4381746893","title":"EMEA Service Director","company":"Leica Microsystems","location":"Wetzlar","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://danaher.wd1.myworkdayjobs.com/DanaherJobs/job/FRA---Remote/EMEA-Service-Director_R1306997/apply?source=APPLICANT_SOURCE_LINKEDIN_POSTING","description":"For over 175 years, Leica Microsystems has helped shape the future by developing ground-breaking optical and digital solutions. As a global leader, we’re driven by continuous improvement to excite our customers and to create the best work environment for our people. Customer focus, innovation, and teamwork are at the core of our culture and the foundation of our success.\n\nLeica Microsystems is one of the market leaders in the fields of microscopy, imaging, and analysis. We reveal the invisible and empower our customers to create a better and healthier world. Together with our customers, we transform scientific discovery. We empower surgeons to take well-informed decisions in life-changing procedures. We enable users to gain insights which help answer key questions concerning development and engineering. All of this is achieved with the combination of cutting-edge microscopes and AI-based image analysis.\n\nWant to be part of a company whose products are part of cutting-edge research around the world? Join Leica Microsystems in our commitment for brilliant solutions and insight.\n\nLeica Microsystems is one of 10 Life Sciences companies of Danaher. Together, we accelerate the discovery, development and delivery of solutions that safeguard and improve human health.\n\nWe currently offer the following position in any major European location which will be REMOTE : Service Director, EMEA\n\nAre you passionate about building, developing and managing an organization that strives to be best in class? Do you enjoy excelling in customer satisfaction and improving quality by driving to the root cause of product and process issues? We are seek