{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4395872542","title":"Senior Manager, Government Affairs Saudi Arabia","company":"Oracle","location":"Austin","remote":false,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://eeho.fa.us2.oraclecloud.com/hcmUI/CandidateExperience/en/job/330480/?utm_medium=jobboard&utm_source=linkedin","description":"Job Description\n\nJob Details\n\nOracle Corporation is a global leader in enterprise software, cloud computing, artificial intelligence, and database technologies. Building on its longstanding leadership in database systems, Oracle now offers a comprehensive portfolio of cloud infrastructure, enterprise applications, and AI-powered solutions that support organizations across both the private and public sectors worldwide.\n\nOrganizations around the world partner with Oracle to accelerate digital transformation, modernize legacy infrastructure, and strengthen critical digital infrastructure. Through its secure and flexible cloud platforms—including distributed and sovereign cloud solutions—Oracle helps public and private sector customers address key priorities such as data sovereignty, cybersecurity, operational efficiency, and the responsible use of data and AI.\n\nJob Description\n\nSenior Manager, Government Affairs Saudi Arabia\n\nOracle Corporate Affairs leads Oracle’s engagements with policy makers worldwide seeking to ensure a regulatory environment conducive to the growth of Oracle’s business. The Corporate Affairs team includes representatives in Washington DC, Europe, Africa, Middle East, Asia and Latin America. We are creating a new position for a Senior Manager, Government Affairs Saudi Arabia who will be based in our Oracle office in Riyadh (KSA) reporting to the Director, Government Affairs for Middle East. He/She will lead and coordinate Oracle’s engagement with government officials, trade associations and other key policy stakeholders, working closely with Oracle’s senior management in Middle East, ensuring Oracle is viewed as a constructive and credible contributor to national digital priorities.\n\nHe/She will work closely with colleagues in Oracle’s legal, compliance, corporate communication, and standards divisions, as well as with business leaders in Oracle’s cloud operations and global business units, to ensure a coordinated approach that advances Oracle’s business objectives and strengthens regulatory trust.\n\nRole and Responsibilities\n\n Policy Strategy: Identify regulatory initiatives in Saudi Arabia that could have a material impact on Oracle’s business, or the interests of our customers. Develop strategic plans - including on a cross-functional basis when required - to leverage opportunities and resolve challenges. Identify and engage allies, foster coordination, and build coalitions to drive policy change. Political outreach: Expand and manage Oracle’s relations with Saudi government officials and relevant stakeholders to maintain Oracle’s reputation as a trusted and credible contributor on policy issues. Represent Oracle before public institutions, trade associations, think-tanks, and industry coalitions. Business risk & opportunities: Anticipate new regulations in the Kingdom and work with Oracle business leaders to ensure they are apprised of relevant public policy developments. Work with a cross functional group of colleagues from the legal, security, privacy, compliance, sustainability teams to develop policy positions on relevant issues for Oracle, including, but not limited to, cloud computing, digital regulation, digital sovereignty, cyber security, data privacy, data center and tax.\n\n\nProfessional Competencies:\n\nRequired:\n\n 8+ years of relevant work experience in a highly professional environment focused on policy or government work. At least 3+ years of experience in Saudi Arabia. High-tech industry or related experience. Good understanding of tech policy issues including Cloud, data privacy, security, AI and trade. Expertise in navigating the political landscape and policy-making landscape in Saudi Arabia. A proven track record to lead and deliver multiple initiatives simultaneously. Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with accuracy and attention to detail. An enquiring mind, eager to continuously learn about the ever-evolving technology landscape. Excellent verbal and written communication skills in Arabic and English. Ability to collaborate effectively with colleagues across departments and regions in different time zones Comfortable working in a virtual team environment, independently and under tight guidelines. Strong team player, highly motivated and willing to provide help where needed to ensure the success of the team.\n\n\nQualifications\n\nCareer Level - IC5\n\nAbout Us\n\nOnly Oracle brings together the data, infrastructure, applications, and expertise to power everything from industry innovations to life-saving care. And with AI embedded across our products and services, we help customers turn that promise into a better future for all. Discover your potential at a company leading the way in AI and cloud solutions that impact billions of lives.\n\nTrue innovation starts when everyone is empowered to contribute. That’s why we’re committed to growing a workforce that promotes opportunities for all with competitive benefits that support our people with flexible medical, life insurance, and retirement options. We also encourage employees to give back to their communities through our volunteer programs.\n\nWe’re committed to including people with disabilities at all stages of the employment process. If you require accessibility assistance or accommodation for a disability at any point, let us know by emailing accommodation-request_mb@oracle.com or by calling 1-888-404-2494 in the United States.\n\nOracle is an Equal Employment Opportunity Employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity, disability and protected veterans’ status, or any other characteristic protected by law. Oracle will consider for employment qualified applicants with arrest and conviction records pursuant to applicable law."}
