ve sustainable growth and in doing so we touch the lives of many across the globe.\n\nOur Excellence Behaviours: Client-centric, Agile, Collaborative. These three behaviours represent how we do things at BSI. They help us ensure that BSI is a great place to work and a highly successful business.\n\nD&I Policy \n\nBSI is committed to ensuring the diversity of our workforce reflects that of our clients and the communities in which we operate. Our goal is to create a sense of belonging for all employees by providing opportunities to develop, grow, and engage with our global organization all while having fun doing great work. BSI is a community where everyone can thrive.\n\nIf you require any reasonable accommodations to be made on account of a disability or impairment throughout out our recruiting process, please inform your Talent Acquisition Partner.\n\nAbout Us\n\nBSI is a business improvement and standards company and for over a century BSI has been recognized for having a positive impact on organizations and society, building trust and enhancing lives.\n\nToday BSI partners with more than 77,500 clients in 195 countries and engages with a 15,000 strong global community of experts, industry and consumer groups, organizations and governments.\n\nUtilizing its extensive expertise in key industry sectors - including automotive, aerospace, built environment, food and retail, and healthcare - BSI delivers on its purpose by helping its clients fulfil theirs.\n\nLiving by our core values of Client-Centricity, Agility, and Collaboration, BSI provides organizations with the confidence to grow by partnering with them to tackle society’s critical issues – from climate change to building trust in digital transformation and everything in between - to accelerate progress towards a better society and a sustainable world.\n\nBSI is an Equal Opportunity Employer dedicated to fostering a diverse and inclusive workplace.\n\n"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4365564938","title":"Business Solutions Architect - IoT & Smart Containers","company":"ORBCOMM","location":"Sterling","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://workforcenow.adp.com/mascsr/default/mdf/recruitment/recruitment.html?cid=b9e6f585-387b-496e-8b63-bee5bed64c3e&ccId=19000101_000001&type=JS&lang=en_US&jobId=580320&rb=LinkedIn","description":"Join Us as a Business Solutions Architect - IoT & Smart Containers! \n\nAre you ready to turn complex business needs into future-ready solutions for global maritime leaders? At ORBCOMM, we’re looking for a highly skilled Business Solutions Architect to transform ideas into action and accelerate customer ROI for our Smart Containers line of business.\n\nWhy You’ll Love Working Here\n\nAs a key member of ORBCOMM’s International Sales team, you’ll be a strategic, customer-facing technical expert at the intersection of customer success and solution delivery. You’ll combine deep technical expertise with hands-on execution to lead solution design, PoCs, and pilots while guiding customers through architectural decisions that deliver business value.\n\nIn this high-impact role, you’ll design, deploy, and optimize solutions that deliver real-time visibility, reduce operational losses, and position ORBCOMM as a trusted partner. Your insights will influence product evolution through structured Voice of Customer (VoC) feedback, ensuring our solutions meet real-world needs.\n\nYou’ll collaborate closely with Customer Success Managers (CSMs) on strategic accounts to ensure successful deployments, measurable outcomes, and long-term adoption. You’ll uncover blind spots and turn them into actionable insights at scale.\n\nThis role will be based remotely out of any major European city. Enjoy the freedom of remote work while staying connected—collaborate virtually with our global teams from the comfort of your home.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\nSupport Strategic Customers Across EuropeServe as the primary technical architect for Smart Container solutions, ensuring timely deployments and responsiveness to local needsPartner with E-CSMs on large maritime and intermodal accounts to drive onboarding, expansion, and optimizationBuild strong relationships with customer stakeholders, from technical teams to executive leadership, across Europe’s leading carriersDesign and Deliver Future-Ready SolutionsConduct technical discovery to baseline current architectures, integrations, and operational processesDesign scalable, secure solution architectures aligned with customer goals and ORBCOMM’s Smart Container capabilitiesCreate architecture diagrams, integration specifications, and data design documentation to support deploymentsLead Deployments and Pilot ProgramsDrive integration, configuration, testing, and validation of Smart Container solutions in customer environmentsOwn successful delivery of PoCs and pilots with clear success criteria and measurable outcomesCoordinate execution with cross-functional teams and prepare implementation plans, test scripts, and acceptance documentationProvide Technical Leadership and Customer Guidance Act as a trusted advisor—guiding architectural decisions that maximize operational efficiency and ROI.Translate complex technical concepts into clear, value-driven narratives for business leaders.Share best practices and coach customers on workflows, integration patterns, and system utilization.Capture Voice of Customer and Influence Product DirectionGather actionable insights from deployments, PoCs, and customer discussions to identify solution gaps.Provide structured feedback to Product Management and Engineering to shape roadmap priorities.Advocate for enhancements based on regional needs and industry trends.Collaborate Across Functions to Drive SuccessWork closely with E-CSMs on account plans, expansion opportunities, and technical escalations.Partner with Product, Engineering, RevOps, Sales Engineering, and Support to ensure solution feasibility and alignment.Contribute to internal knowledge bases, best practices, and reusable solution assets.\nWho You Are:  \n\nYou’re a strategic problem-solver with deep technical expertise and sharp business acumen, ready to turn complexity into clarity and deliver results with agility and precision.\n\nIf you have: \n\nA bachelor’s degree in Engineering, Business, Marketing, or related field (MBA preferred).5–8+ years in solution architecture, technical consulting, system integration, or SaaS/IoT solution delivery, with enterprise-level experience.Expertise in cloud services, APIs, data models, networking, and enterprise IT ecosystems, plus hands-on experience deploying software, integrations, or IoT systems.Industry experience in logistics, transportation, supply chain, maritime, or industrial IoT.Proven ability to assess current-state systems, design future-state architectures, and deliver PoCs, pilots, and technical projects.Certifications in cloud or architecture frameworks (AWS, Azure, TOGAF, etc.), and familiarity with scripting, integration platforms, or data engineering.Strong communication and stakeholder influence skills, with a collaborative, customer-focused mindset.Analytical and adaptable, able to navigate complexity while balancing strategic design and hands-on execution. Ability to manage multiple regional engagements and collaborate with global teams on multi-region deployments.Comfort with AI-enabled tools and automation, and a commitment to continuous learning in digital and AI literacy.Multilingual proficiency (fluency in three languages strongly preferred).Willingness to travel internationally (up to 20%).\n\nThen we want to meet you!  \n\nThe Benefits Of Working Here\n\nA career with ORBCOMM offers a unique opportunity to grow your skills and expand your expertise in a collaborative, innovative environment. Beyond being part of an exceptional team, we provide a competitive, locally relevant benefits package designed to support our employees