g global growth and opportunity.\n\nTether Evolution: At the intersection of technology and human potential, we are pushing the boundaries of what is possible, crafting a future where innovation and human capabilities merge in powerful, unprecedented ways.\n\nWhy Join Us?\n\nOur team is a global talent powerhouse, working remotely from every corner of the world. If you’re passionate about making a mark in the fintech space, this is your opportunity to collaborate with some of the brightest minds, pushing boundaries and setting new standards. We’ve grown fast, stayed lean, and secured our place as a leader in the industry.\n\nIf you have excellent English communication skills and are ready to contribute to the most innovative platform on the planet, Tether is the place for you.\n\nAre you ready to be part of the future?\n\nAbout the job:\n\nIn this role, you will require a deep understanding of technology, excellent stakeholder management, and the ability to guide cross-functional teams through the product lifecycle. You’ll collaborate with developers, designers, and leadership to define product roadmaps, align on requirements, and launch new products. This is a great opportunity for someone with great experience, to contribute to impactful product launches in a highly dynamic environment.\n\nKey responsibilities:\n\nProduct development and Roadmap: Lead the end-to-end product lifecycle from ideation and requirements gathering to delivery and post-launch analysis. Define user stories, acceptance criteria, perform backlog management and workflows for development teams.\nTechnical Expertise: Translate complex technical concepts into clear, actionable product requirements. Evaluate technical solutions and prioritize features based on technical feasibility, business impact, and customer value.\nConduct extensive market research, including customer discovery to understand the value proposition of our product.\nCross-Functional Collaboration: Work with developers, designers, and other stakeholders to gather requirements, validate and deliver solutions.\nQuality & Delivery: Ensure product features are delivered on time and meet quality standards; organize testing and feedback loops.\n\nMandatory:\n\n5+ years of product management experience with at least 3 years in a technical product management role.\nExcellent communication skills for bridging technical and non-technical stakeholders.\nExpertise in agile methodologies - Jira, Asana etc.\nStrong understanding of microservices, peer-to-peer systems, javascript.\nStrong organizational skills to balance multiple priorities in a fast-paced, remote environment.\nSkilled in defining, tracking, and reporting on product KPIs to measure success; expertise in A/B testing or similar experimentation methods is a plus.\n\nPreferred:\n\nExperience leading AI and peer-to-peer (P2P) projects.\nHands-on development experience with JavaScript (e.g., frameworks like Node.js, React, or Angular)"}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=144bf973fc229440","title":"Design Manager - MEP","company":"AtkinsRéalis","location":"{\"city\":\"Abu Dhabi\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Abu Dhabi\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Abu Dhabi\",\"latitude\":24.46,\"longitude\":54.36,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"6 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=144bf973fc229440","description":"Overview\n\nAtkinsRéalis seeks an MEP Design Manager who will be responsible for overseeing the design, coordination, and integration of MEP systems within building projects. This role ensures that MEP designs meet all technical, regulatory, and project requirements from concept through construction, while managing consultants, and stakeholder interfaces.\n\nYour role\nLead and manage the MEP design process across all project stages—concept, schematic, detailed design, and construction.\nCoordinate between architectural, structural, and MEP disciplines to ensure fully integrated designs.\nReview and approve MEP design documents, calculations, specifications, and drawings for quality, accuracy, and compliance.\nManage external MEP consultants and internal teams to meet project goals and timelines.\nEnsure designs comply with local codes, international standards, and sustainability requirements.\nOversee design submissions, technical reports, and authority approvals.\nFacilitate design workshops, technical meetings, and value engineering sessions.\nSupport procurement by providing technical input during tender reviews and supplier evaluations.\nResolve technical issues during construction and provide support for site implementation.\nAbout you\nBachelor's degree in Mechanical or Electrical Engineering (Master's preferred).\n15+ years of experience in MEP design and coordination, with at least 3 years in a managerial role.\nExperience in large-scale or residential projects in UAE\nPrevious PMC experience is a must\nStrong knowledge of building systems, codes, and standards.\nProficient in AutoCAD, Revit MEP, and relevant design and coordination tools.\nExcellent communication, leadership, and problem-solving skills.\nCertification or membership in relevant professional bodies\nFamiliarity with BIM workflows and clash detection platforms (e.g., Navisworks)\nRewards & benefits\n\nExplore the rewards and benefits that help you thrive – at every stage of your life and your career.\n\nThis includes:\n\nTax-free salary.\nComprehensive life insurance coverage.\nPremium medical insurance for you and your dependents.\nGenerous annual leave balance.\nFlexible and hybrid work solutions.\nRemote work opportunities outside of country.\nCompany gratuity scheme.\nDiscretionary bonus program.\nAnnual flight contribution.\nRelocation assistance.\nTransportation & housing allowances (available for remote work locations)\nEmployee Wellbeing Program: 24/7 access to specialists in finance, legal matters, family care, personal health, fitness, and nutrition.\n\nSeize every opportunity to sharpen your skills, expand your expertise, and be recognized for the impact you make.\n\nAbout AtkinsRéalis\n\nWe're AtkinsRéalis, a world-class engineering services and nuclear organization. We connect people, data and technology to transform the world's'infrastructure and energy systems. Together, with our industry partners and clients, and our global team of consultants, designers, engineers and project managers, we can change the world. We're committed to leading our clients across our various end markets to engineer a better future for our planet and its people."}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=1692b2fe862f6c3a","title":"Senior Product Manager (Healthcare RCM)","company":"Fatorah Insurance Claims Settlement L.L.C","location":"{\"city\":\"Remote\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Remote\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Remote\",\"latitude\":25,\"longitude\":-40,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":true,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"2 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=1692b2fe862f6c3a","description":"*Title: Senior Product Manager (Healthcare RCM)*\n\nLocation: [Location/Remote]\n\nReporting to: *CEO / Head of Product*\n\nRole Summary:\n\nWe are seeking a strategic and technical Product Manager to lead the evolution of our Health Claim Management Solution. In this role, you will act as the bridge between our Business stakeholders and our specialized Engineering teams (Backend, AI/ML, Data). You will own the product roadmap for the UAE and KSA markets, translating complex regulatory requirements (NAPHIES, Malaffi) into detailed, actionable user stories for development.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\nProduct Strategy & Roadmap:\n\nDefine and execute the product roadmap, balancing regulatory compliance (KSA/UAE), customer feature requests, and technical debt.\n\nIdentify high-value opportunities to leverage our AI/ML capabilities (e.g., automated coding, fraud detection, predictive analytics) and define the acceptance criteria for these models.\n\nRequirement Engineering (User Stories):\n\nTranslate high-level business requirements into extensive user stories and user journeys.\n\nCreate detailed functional specifications and acceptance criteria (BDD/Gherkin) for the Backend, Frontend, and QC teams.\n\nMaintain a groomed backlog in Jira/Azure DevOps, ensuring the engineering team always has ready-to-work tasks.\n\nMarket & Compliance Alignment:\n\nServe as the subject matter expert for UAE (Malaffi, Nabidh) and KSA (NAPHIES, CHI) regulatory changes, ensuring the product remains compliant ahead of deadlines.\n\nManage the integration roadmap for third-party payers and aggregators (waseel, dhaman, etc.).\n\nCross-Functional Leadership:\n\nCollaborate with the Data Architect to define analytics requirements and dashboard needs for clients.\n\nWork with the QC Team to validate that delivered features meet the strict \"Definition of Done.\"\n\nClient & Implementation Oversight:\n\nLead the \"Product\" side of client implementations, configuring the system workflow to match client SOPs.\n\nConduct product demos and training sessions for key stakeholders in Arabic and English.\n\nRequirements:\n\nExperience: 5+ years in Product Management within Healthcare IT, specifically Revenue Cycle Management (RCM) or Health Insurance.\n\nDomain Knowledge: Deep understanding of medical coding (ICD-10-AM, CPT, ACHI), claim cycles (e-Claims, Remittance), and approvals.\n\nTechnical Fluency:\n\nAbility to read and understand API documentation (Swagger/Postman). You do not need to code, but you must understand data flow, JSON structures, and integration points.\n\nExperience managing products that utilize AI/ML features is a strong plus.\n\nLanguage: Native or Professional proficiency in Arabic and English is mandatory for client interactions in KSA/UAE.\n\nDocumentation Skills: Exceptional skill in writing clear, concise technical documentation and user guides.\n\nSoft Skills: Strong negotiation skills to manage stakeholder expectations and ability to explain technical constraints to non-technical business leaders.\n\nNice to Have:\n\nExperience with PostgreSQL (running basic queries to validate data).\n\nCertification in Product Management (CSPO, AIPMM).\n\nExperience with UI/UX prototyping tools (Figma, Balsamiq) to convey ideas to the Frontend team.\n\nJob Types: Full-time, Permanent\n\nPay: From AED1.00 per month"}
