act as a co-founder of the business, driving the product strategy and leading a passionate squad to solve customer problems and deliver meaningful value. This is a high-impact role that blends business acumen with technical expertise, requiring you to craft and execute a bold vision while navigating complex dependencies across the Everything App.\n\nBeyond B2C, you’ll also shape and scale key partnerships with banks, telecoms, and other tech or membership programs to grow the business.\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\nLead end-to-end product initiatives, from ideation to launch and impact measurement.\n\nOwn and deliver complex features with dependencies across the Super App, ensuring timely delivery and measurable customer value.\n\nSupport the Head of Product in defining and executing the product roadmap and long-term strategy.\n\nUse market research, industry trends, and deep customer understanding to shape Careem Plus’ growth.\n\nBe data-driven in testing hypotheses and uncovering opportunities within the Careem ecosystem.\n\nBuild strong relationships across teams to ensure alignment and deliver a seamless, end-to-end member experience.\n\nFoster a culture of open communication, feedback, and product excellence within the squad.\n\nWhat You’ll Need\n\nExperience: 3–5 years in product management, ideally in customer-facing applications.\n\nAI & Automation: Proven ability to leverage AI to optimize product lifecycle automation and enhance product features.\n\nData Proficiency: Strong analytical skills with hands-on SQL expertise to extract insights, validate hypotheses, and analyze experiment results.\n\nProduct Mindset: Passion for building great products and solving complex, high-impact problems.\n\nLeadership & Collaboration: Skilled at rallying cross-functional teams to achieve ambitious goals, and influencing external partners whose priorities may not directly align.\n\nCustomer Empathy: Ability to deeply understand and design for diverse customer needs and circumstances.\n\nCommunication: Strong facilitation skills with the ability to foster constructive dialogue within teams and effectively engage with senior leadership.\n\nWhat we’ll provide you\n\nWe offer colleagues the opportunity to drive impact in the region while they learn and grow. As a full time Careem colleague, you will be able to:\n\nWork and learn from great minds by joining a community of inspiring colleagues.\n\nPut your passion to work in a purposeful organisation dedicated to creating impact in a region with a lot of untapped potential.\n\nExplore new opportunities to learn and grow every day.\n\nWork 4 days a week in office & 1 day from home, and remotely from any country in the world for 30 days a year with unlimited vacation days per year. (If you are in an individual contributor role in tech, you will have 2 office days a week and 3 to work from home.)\n\nAccess to healthcare benefits and fitness reimbursements for health activities including gym, health club, and training classes."}
