{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=9c04c1d68dfdcae1","title":"Senior Legal Counsel","company":"UMO","location":"{\"city\":\"Dubai\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Dubai\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Dubai\",\"latitude\":25.20485,\"longitude\":55.270782,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"3 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=9c04c1d68dfdcae1","description":"About Us\n\nUMO is a stealth-mode FinTech venture aiming to evolve the way people experience money by building a unified, AI-powered, yet deeply human modern money platform across fiat, crypto, and investments - subject to regulatory approvals. The platform is being designed to break down traditional barriers to money across access, assets, and experience, enabling simpler, more adaptive ways for people to interact with financial services.\n\nWe are currently developing our MVP and navigating licensing requirements, with a multidisciplinary team of 100+ people representing 20+ nationalities. With our headquarters in the UAE and offices in Portugal and Ukraine, we are united behind a shared ambition and a relentless focus\n\nWhat You'll Do\n\nAs a Senior Legal Counsel, you will lead and grow a team of 2 experienced legal specialists to deliver high-quality, secure, and compliant solutions in a regulated fintech environment. You will play a key role in shaping the legal function, driving delivery excellence, and ensuring that innovation is balanced with governance and risk management.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\nProvide expert legal counsel on all aspects of the finance platform’s operations, focusing on the convergence of traditional finance, payments, and digital assets (crypto).\nOwn and manage the legal and compliance roadmap for expansion into new target markets, including the UAE and MENA region.\nDraft, review, and negotiate complex commercial contracts, partnership agreements (processors, payment schemes, and exchanges), and vendor contracts.\nEnsure the platform, including products like cards, wallets, and trading features, complies with local and international financial regulations (e.g., AML, KYC, data privacy).\nAdvise senior management on corporate governance, licensing requirements, and risk mitigation strategies in a multi-jurisdictional environment.\nManage regulatory inquiries and external counsel engagement across key operational geographies.\nCreate global contract lifecycle management (CLM) processes, including template standardization, review workflows, and a definitive repository for all executed documents.\nDevelop, implement, and audit all employment contracts and policies, ensuring strict compliance with UAE Labour Law (including DIFC/ADGM) and EU labor directives.\nAdvise HR on complex employment matters, including disciplinary procedures, statutory termination requirements, and end-of-service gratuity calculations (UAE).\nManage global workforce legalities, including independent contractor classification, remote work policies, and enforceable non-compete/non-solicitation clauses.\nMaintain and enforce the global corporate structure (subsidiary registrations, intercompany agreements) and guarantee all corporate filing deadlines are met.\nOversee data protection and privacy compliance efforts, including GDPR standards for EU operations and equivalent mandates in the UAE/MENA region.\n\nYou’re a Perfect Fit If You Have:\n\n7+ years of experience as a Legal Counsel, with a strong focus on the financial services sector.\nSolid experience in a regulated FinTech, Banking, or Crypto company is mandatory.\nProven track record of managing and mentoring junior legal staff or leading a small legal team (ideally 3+ people).\nDeep understanding of payments regulation (e.g., SEPA/SWIFT, card schemes), digital asset laws, and licensing procedures in key jurisdictions.\nExceptional drafting and negotiation skills.\n\nProficiency in English (B2-C1), both written and verbal (knowledge of Ukrainian or Russian is an advantage).\n\nCompensation & Benefits (Dubai, UAE):\n\nHighly Competitive Compensation.\n\nVisa Sponsorship: Full coverage of UAE employment visa and residency permit costs.\nRelocation Support: Dedicated support desk to assist with your move, including inbound flight coverage (if applicable).\nTime Off: 25 working days of Annual Leave + UAE Public Holidays.\nHealth Coverage: Comprehensive Medical Insurance for yourself.\nPerformance Incentives: Eligibility for performance-based bonuses and incentives.\nStatutory Benefits: End of Service Gratuity as per UAE Labour Law.\n\nShape the future: join a successful, next-generation modern money platform!"}
