{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4394302495","title":"Controller US Vacation Rentals","company":"TALENTMATE","location":"Sharjah","remote":false,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://www.talentmate.com/jobs/uae/dubai/controller-us-vacation-rentals/2604-14740-33","description":"Job Description\n\nHoward Financial is a full-service back-office solution for high-growth companies with bookkeeping, payroll, and bespoke reporting needs that require accuracy, timeliness, and institutional-quality reporting without the burden of full-time staff. We are an experienced team of bookkeepers and administrators with multiple decades of combined experience across industries allowing companies to focus on their core business while we handle the rest.\n\nFounded in 2023, our team of ~100 professionals supports ~75 clients across a diverse range of industries. We recently reached $6M of contracted ARR and are growing rapidly (over 200% LTM growth).\n\nAs a Controller at Howard, you will be responsible for the financial integrity of a portfolio of Vacation Rental clients. You will bridge the gap between day-to-day bookkeeping and executive-level financial strategy. This role requires a professional who deeply understands the unique accounting challenges of the Short-Term Rental (STR) industry, including trust accounting, owner statements, and merchant processing reconciliations.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nFinancial Oversight: Manage the full month-end close process for multiple STR clients, ensuring Profit & Loss statements and Balance Sheets are accurate and ready for leadership review.Trust Accounting & Owner Statements: Oversee the reconciliation of guest payments, security deposits, and cleaning fees. Ensure owner statements are generated accurately and distributions are processed on time.KPI Analysis: Track and report on industry-specific metrics such as RevPAR (Revenue Per Available Room), ADR (Average Daily Rate), and Occupancy rates to provide actionable insights to clients.Audit & Compliance: Review the work performed by staff accountants and bookkeepers, ensuring all entries align with US GAAP and client-specific Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs).System Integration: Manage data flow between Property Management Systems (PMS) like Guesty, Hostaway, or Streamline and accounting platforms (QuickBooks Online/NetSuite).Client Communication: Serve as the primary point of contact for financial inquiries, explaining variances and providing clarity on financial performance during monthly reviews.\n\nRequirements & Qualifications\n\nIndustry Experience (MANDATORY): At least 4+ years of direct experience as an Accountant or Senior Accountant specifically within the US Vacation Rental / Short-Term Rental (STR) industry.Accounting Foundation: Bachelor’s degree in Accounting or Finance. A solid understanding of US GAAP is required.Technical Stack: Advanced proficiency in QuickBooks Online and experience with at least one PMS (e.g., Guesty, Hostaway, Streamline, Track).Analytical Skills: Expert-level Excel skills (VLOOKUPs, Pivot Tables, data cleaning) for reconciling complex reservation reports.English Proficiency: Exceptional written and verbal communication skills (C1/C2 level) for direct client interaction.Growth Mindset: Ability to work in a fast-paced environment and adapt to new technologies and client workflows quickly.\n\nWhat We Offer\n\nCompetitive Compensation: Fixed monthly payment in US Dollars.Performance Incentives: Quarterly bonuses based on performance and quality metrics.Career Path: Bi-annual reviews (July & December) with opportunities to transition into a Senior Controller or Vertical Lead role.Flexibility: 100% remote work with a supportive global culture.Time Off: 10 paid national holidays per year and unlimited PTO after 6 months of tenure.\n\nJob Details\n\nRole Level: Mid-Level Work Type: Full-Time Country: United Arab Emirates City: Dubai Company Website: https://www.financebyhoward.com/ Job Function: Finance Company Industry/\n\nSector: Financial Services\n\nWhat We Offer\n\nAbout The Company\n\nSearching, interviewing and hiring are all part of the professional life. The TALENTMATE Portal idea is to fill and help professionals doing one of them by bringing together the requisites under One Roof. Whether you're hunting for your Next Job Opportunity or Looking for Potential Employers, we're here to lend you a Helping Hand.\n\nReport\n\nDisclaimer: talentmate.com is only a platform to bring jobseekers & employers together. Applicants are advised to research the bonafides of the prospective employer independently. We do NOT endorse any requests for money payments and strictly advice against sharing personal or bank related information. We also recommend you visit Security Advice for more information. If you suspect any fraud or malpractice, email us at abuse@talentmate.com."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4394304650","title":"Enterprise Solution Engineer - Indian Market International Solutions Engineer Team","company":"TALENTMATE","location":"Sharjah","remote":false,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://www.talentmate.com/jobs/uae/dubai/enterprise-solution-engineer-indian-market-international-solutions-engineer-team/2603-3237-66","description":"Job Description\n\nAre you ready to be part of something big? We’re hiring for the Enterprise Solution Engineer - Indian market (International Solutions Engineer Team) on our Sales Team!\n\nIn this role, you’ll engage with key decision-makers, forge impactful relationships with some of the world’s most influential organizations, and directly contribute to the growth of Semrush.\n\nWhy Semrush?\n\nWe are a global leader in online marketing technology, meeting market demand with rapid scaling. Don’t miss the chance to join our unstoppable momentum and make history with us!\n\nSome Highlights Of Our Success Include\n\nSemrush named a Leader in The Forrester Wave™: Search Engine Optimization Solutions, Q3 2025$400M+ Annual Recurring Revenue118,000+ paying customers worldwide1M+ freemium usersExceptional demand for our new Enterprise platform, with deals secured from global giants like P&G, Tesla, FedEx, Samsung, Amazon, and others. \n\nIf youre looking for a role where your impact will be visible and meaningful, we’d love to hear from you.\n\nTasks in the role\n\nBe a thought leader to the sales team and a technical lead on strategic client relationships across various industry verticals.Act as a trusted advisor to our customers, identifying and developing new business opportunities that align with their objectives.Build and maintain strong strategic relationships with account teams, partners, and customers to support sales objectives.Collaborate with sales teams to assess potential deals, determine customer needs, and identify the best approach for engagement.Conduct deep-dive discussions and discoveries with prospects to uncover pain points and understand workflows, use cases and technical requirementsDeliver customized and engaging product demonstrations that illustrate the value of Semrush’s solutions, positioning them against competitors where needed, incorporating real-world examples and addressing customer-specific challenges.Take ownership of the technical solution validation during the sales process by leading technical assessments, proof of concepts, objection handling, buyer enablement and more.Provide authoritative guidance on technical concepts, with expertise in API, data handling, integrations, security, and processes.Collaborate with Executives, Product, Sales, and other senior-level stakeholders to champion an environment for ongoing strategic customer success.Ensure smooth transition from pre-sales to post-sales, providing insights and recommendations to customer success teams for ongoing success.Establish a deep understanding of Semrush’s technology portfolio and its competitive landscape and analyze market trends to effectively position Semrush as the leading choice for customers.Participate in non-deal related activities such as internal training, webinars, events, and collaborate with other Semrush teams on initiatives to drive customer success.\n\nWhat we’re looking for\n\nProven experience working with India-based Enterprise customers is a must.Native English speaker (proficiency in languages of India is a strong plus).5-8 years of experience in Technical Pre-Sales, Post-Sales, or Sales / Solutions Engineering within a SaaS company.2-3 years of experience in mid-market or enterprise sales, with a track record of closing complex deals > €250K ARR.Proficiency in sales methodologies such as Sandler, Challenger, SPIN, MEDDPICC, etc.Strong sense of ownership and experience leading the technical solution validation of a deal.Exceptional collaboration skills and an organizational and structured approach.Customer-first mindset with a passion for delivering exceptional customer experiences.Strong communication skills, with the ability to interact confidently with clients.Digital marketing knowledge (e.g. SEO, PPC, Content Marketing, Social, consumer behavior, etc.) highly preferred.Ability to thrive in a fast-paced, team-oriented environment.A Bachelor degree is preferred (e.g. engineering, business administration or similar field), or equivalent experience.\n\nA Bit About The Team\n\nThe Sales team is at the forefront of empowering businesses to achieve online visibility and digital marketing success.\n\nThrough Our One Semrush Selling Approach And World-class Enablement Programs, We Equip Our Team With The Tools, Resources, And Training Needed To\n\nExceed sales goalsMaximize earning potentialDeliver meaningful results for our clients\n\nTo learn more about our business and vision, explore the Semrush Analyst Day 2024 presentation from New York City.\n\nWhat’s In It For You\n\nFlexible working hoursUnlimited PTOFlexi Benefit for your hobbyEmployee Support ProgramLoss of family member financial aidEmployee Resource GroupsMeals, snacks, and drinks at the officeCorporate eventsTeambuildingTraining, courses, conferences\n\nA Little More About Our Company\n\nSemrush is a leading online visibility management SaaS platform that enables businesses globally to run search engine optimization, pay-per-click, content, social media and competitive research campaigns and get measurable results from online marketing.\n\nWeve been developing our product for 17 years and have been awarded G2s Top 100 Software Products, Global and US Search Awards 2021, Great Place to Work Certification, Deloitte Technology Fast 500 and many more. In March 2021 Semrush went public and started trading on the NYSE with the SEMR ticker.\n\n10,000,000+ users in America, Europe, Asia, and Australia have already tried Semrush, and over 1,700 people around the world are working on its development. The Semrush team is constantly growing.\n\nOur Diversity, Equity, and Inclusion commitments \n\nSemrush is an equal opportunity employer. Building a better future for marketers around the world unites people from all backgrounds. Even if you feel that you don’t 100% match all requirements, don’t be discouraged to apply! We are committed to ensure that everyone feels a sense of belonging in the workplace.\n\nWe do not discriminate based upon race, religion, creed, color, national origin, sex, pregnancy, sexual orientation, gender identity, gender expression, age, ancestry, physical or mental disability, or medical condition including medical characteristics, genetic identity, marital status, military service, or any other classification protected by applicable local, state or federal laws.\n\nOur new colleague, we are waiting for you!\n\nApply for this job\n\nSean Ennis\n\nSales Recruiter\n\nsean.ennis@semrush.com\n\nJob Details\n\nRole Level: Mid-Level Work Type: Internship Country: United Arab Emirates City: Dubai Company Website: http://www.semrush.com Job Function: Engineering Company Industry/\n\nSector: Software Development\n\nWhat We Offer\n\nAbout The Company\n\nSearching, interviewing and hiring are all part of the professional life. The TALENTMATE Portal idea is to fill and help professionals doing one of them by bringing together the requisites under One Roof. Whether you're hunting for your Next Job Opportunity or Looking for Potential Employers, we're here to lend you a Helping Hand.\n\nReport\n\nDisclaimer: talentmate.com is only a platform to bring jobseekers & employers together. Applicants are advised to research the bonafides of the prospective employer independently. We do NOT endorse any requests for money payments and strictly advice against sharing personal or bank related information. We also recommend you visit Security Advice for more information. If you suspect any fraud or malpractice, email us at abuse@talentmate.com."}
